1
00:00:36,680 --> 00:00:38,040
Is it too short?

2
00:03:29,560 --> 00:03:31,760
<i>Uh, I've arrived at the hotel.</i>

3
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:33,240
<i>Are you coming down now?</i>

4
00:03:33,320 --> 00:03:36,920
<i>Then call Det to come up</i>
<i>and take care of his girlfriend.</i>

5
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:40,120
<i>I'm tired,</i>
<i>so I came down to grab a drink at the bar.</i>

6
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:42,560
<i>Come meet me here.</i>

7
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:45,640
Nice, boy.

8
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:47,000
Cheers.

9
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:56,920
Hello?

10
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:59,440
Kluay's phone is with me.

11
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:04,240
Ameena.

12
00:04:08,040 --> 00:04:10,120
Why did Kluay say you were already asleep?

13
00:04:10,760 --> 00:04:13,200
I tried to sleep, but I couldn't,

14
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:15,560
so I asked Kluay to come down for a drink.

15
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:20,519
Drink some water first.

16
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:23,520
Where's Kluay?

17
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:26,760
She went up to get something.
She said she forgot something.

18
00:04:26,840 --> 00:04:28,440
But she'll be back down soon.

19
00:04:36,840 --> 00:04:38,320
Where did you say Kluay was?

20
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:40,680
How did I end up here?

21
00:05:41,880 --> 00:05:44,120
Did you drink in Hua Hin last night?

22
00:05:44,640 --> 00:05:46,080
You were completely drunk.

23
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:50,400
That's a lie.

24
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:53,480
I didn't touch
a single drop of alcohol last night.

25
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:58,800
You… What did you put in my drink?

26
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:01,800
Me? Why would I do anything to you?

27
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:05,960
I tried knocking on Kluay's door,

28
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:10,000
but she was in a deep sleep,
so I brought you here.

29
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:12,760
You're lying.

30
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:14,440
Warat.

31
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:16,640
Warat.

32
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:27,120
I reported it because it's my duty.

33
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:30,640
I'm aware that this is your wife's room.

34
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,800
Warat.

35
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:34,040
Ameena, let go.

36
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:35,200
Listen to me first.

37
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,280
Det.

38
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:47,120
Kluay.

39
00:06:55,960 --> 00:06:57,000
Det.

40
00:07:02,760 --> 00:07:04,000
Last night,

41
00:07:04,520 --> 00:07:06,440
I had a bad feeling about this.

42
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:09,880
Ameena can't be trusted.

43
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:17,640
Come on, Kluay.

44
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:21,000
Don't tell me you believe what Ameena said

45
00:07:21,080 --> 00:07:22,920
just to make us fight.

46
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:28,400
Ameena didn't ask for anything from you.
So why are you reacting like this?

47
00:07:29,280 --> 00:07:30,680
But what everyone saw…

48
00:07:30,760 --> 00:07:34,080
Whatever they saw or think
is their business.

49
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:37,320
If you didn't do anything,
why do you care?

50
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:38,840
Kluay.

51
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:41,400
If you weren't there,
I wouldn't care at all.

52
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:45,480
What? You told me not to overthink,

53
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:47,120
but look at you.

54
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:49,960
Do you really believe that?

55
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:55,480
So now you're saying
I'm the one thinking badly?

56
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:57,560
That's not what I meant.

57
00:07:57,640 --> 00:08:00,080
Then what do you mean?

58
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:03,000
- I mean…
- You just said it yourself

59
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:04,560
that I'm the one thinking badly.

60
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:08,320
That's not it, Kluay.

61
00:08:10,440 --> 00:08:12,560
I think we shouldn't talk right now.

62
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:16,960
Come on, Kluay.

63
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:18,440
Drive.

64
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:29,480
I hear
you've been handling Warat's inheritance

65
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:31,400
pretty well.

66
00:08:34,039 --> 00:08:35,919
I'm just doing what I promised,

67
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:40,559
and for the share we agreed on.

68
00:08:41,760 --> 00:08:44,440
Good. That's more like it.

69
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:46,040
This is how we should talk.

70
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:49,400
Good. Let's talk straight.

71
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:53,680
I'll never forget everything you've
done for me and Aunt Nong.

72
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:55,680
But I'm not a 10-year-old kid anymore.

73
00:08:55,760 --> 00:08:57,160
Business is business.

74
00:08:59,040 --> 00:09:02,600
Part of this,
I consider to be repaying you.

75
00:09:02,680 --> 00:09:06,040
The other part is what I deserve.

76
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:09,600
That's clear. Good.

77
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:14,360
I hope we won't
have to discuss this again.

78
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:15,920
And from now on,

79
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:21,040
you have to let Aunt Nong
go wherever she wants,

80
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:23,800
not keep her stuck at home
and in that flower garden.

81
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:25,240
Me?

82
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:28,440
It's Anong

83
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:32,360
who stays in the garden all day
and in that treasure room.

84
00:09:35,760 --> 00:09:36,720
Or am I wrong, Anong?

85
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:38,520
Say something.

86
00:09:40,640 --> 00:09:42,600
It's my fault, Sin.

87
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:44,800
See?

88
00:09:47,160 --> 00:09:51,520
Sin, where do you want to take me today?

89
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:53,000
Tell me.

90
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:55,560
Uncle Rut won't mind.

91
00:09:58,120 --> 00:10:00,800
I was just getting in a good mood

92
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:04,040
and now it's ruined. Damn it.

93
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:12,680
Sin. Sin.

94
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:14,320
Please.

95
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:24,440
Why are you bringing my clothes?

96
00:10:24,520 --> 00:10:27,160
I'm not staying anywhere overnight.

97
00:10:27,240 --> 00:10:29,640
I have to stay home.
There's still so much to do.

98
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:31,720
I have to take care of Mr. Rut.

99
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:34,160
And wait for the police too, right?

100
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:41,160
Auntie,
we won't keep getting lucky forever.

101
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:20,840
Ameena.

102
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:26,960
If you want to stay here, fine.
I'm leaving.

103
00:11:27,560 --> 00:11:30,080
Then go. Why are you still standing here?

104
00:11:31,920 --> 00:11:33,440
Let me ask you frankly.

105
00:11:33,960 --> 00:11:36,840
You're mad at me,
but you take it out on those two.

106
00:11:36,920 --> 00:11:39,200
- What does that do?
- Satisfaction.

107
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:44,760
Seeing your precious Kluay get hurt,

108
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:50,400
and making you realize how much I matter.

109
00:11:51,280 --> 00:11:54,400
Even without you, I still have Warat.

110
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:58,160
Remember that. Now go.

111
00:11:58,240 --> 00:12:01,120
Do you think what you're doing is right?

112
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:05,760
I think it's worthless,
completely meaningless.

113
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:14,640
Fine, go. And don't ever come back.

114
00:12:14,720 --> 00:12:16,160
Let's just break up.

115
00:12:21,080 --> 00:12:26,400
This treatment helps relax
both the body and the mind,

116
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:29,720
deep down to a psychological level.

117
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:35,560
As for the details,
our specialist will explain everything.

118
00:12:36,080 --> 00:12:37,800
Please come this way.

119
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:39,640
Please.

120
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:05,720
Aunt Nong,
they're taking such good care of you here.

121
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:08,600
Sin, I'm not staying here.

122
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:11,200
Don't think I can't see through you.

123
00:13:11,280 --> 00:13:13,120
I'm not sick.

124
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:14,960
Auntie, if I remember correctly,

125
00:13:15,040 --> 00:13:18,800
the last time
I went to the hospital with you

126
00:13:18,880 --> 00:13:23,240
was when I was in grad school.
And after that, you never went again.

127
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:26,200
Do you think I'm crazy?

128
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:30,160
Back then, I was just stressed.

129
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:33,000
I wasn't crazy.

130
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:35,000
Are you no longer stressed now?

131
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:37,200
Take me home.

132
00:13:39,040 --> 00:13:41,240
Let go. I'm not staying.

133
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:42,200
Aunt Nong,

134
00:13:42,720 --> 00:13:44,280
I'm trying to help you.

135
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:47,000
That police officer,

136
00:13:47,760 --> 00:13:49,840
Arnon, and Kluay.

137
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:53,040
All three of them have similar fates.

138
00:13:53,560 --> 00:13:58,080
And all three of them
are connected to you.

139
00:13:59,720 --> 00:14:01,520
Sin.

140
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:06,440
Do you even realize what you're saying?

141
00:14:08,040 --> 00:14:09,680
You're accusing me of…

142
00:14:09,760 --> 00:14:10,920
Aunt Nong,

143
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:13,680
listen to me.

144
00:14:15,880 --> 00:14:18,200
I'm the one who deleted the CCTV footage.

145
00:14:20,320 --> 00:14:23,840
There was footage
of that captain coming to our house.

146
00:14:24,920 --> 00:14:27,840
But that doesn't mean
I'm the one who poisoned him.

147
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:32,560
I didn't even mention poisoning yet.

148
00:14:39,560 --> 00:14:40,440
Sin…

149
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:43,480
Everything… Everything I did…

150
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:47,800
I did it for us.

151
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:51,400
I did it for you.

152
00:14:51,480 --> 00:14:53,040
- I did it for your mom.
- Alright.

153
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:54,640
Then stop.

154
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:56,840
That's enough.

155
00:14:57,880 --> 00:14:58,960
If you want it this way,

156
00:14:59,040 --> 00:15:01,400
then just report me to the police!

157
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:02,480
Go ahead, have me arrested.

158
00:15:02,560 --> 00:15:04,760
Auntie, stop. Please listen to me.

159
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:07,280
If you really did it for me,

160
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:09,160
then you have to stay here
and get treatment.

161
00:15:09,240 --> 00:15:11,480
Do you understand?
You have to stay here and recover.

162
00:15:11,560 --> 00:15:12,960
I'll take care of everything else.

163
00:15:14,680 --> 00:15:15,840
Aunt Nong.

164
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:17,760
- No.
- Aunt Nong.

165
00:15:17,840 --> 00:15:19,320
Didn't you say

166
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:21,840
you'd stay with me forever?

167
00:15:22,360 --> 00:15:24,920
I only have you.
If you're not with me, who do I have?

168
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:28,400
Didn't you promise my mom
you'd stay with me forever?

169
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:48,680
Please, Auntie.

170
00:15:58,720 --> 00:16:00,160
Fine. Do as you wish.

171
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:02,920
If you want to go rest, then go ahead.

172
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:07,000
So your nephew
won't have to keep nagging me.

173
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:13,680
I'll be fine on my own.

174
00:16:13,760 --> 00:16:17,040
I've practically been taking care
of myself all along anyway.

175
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:19,440
Don't worry.

176
00:16:19,520 --> 00:16:21,960
Go relax and enjoy yourself, Anong.

177
00:16:22,560 --> 00:16:24,440
If anything comes up, just call.

178
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:30,000
<i>What he said is true.</i>

179
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:32,480
<i>That day, Sin wasn't feeling well,</i>

180
00:16:32,560 --> 00:16:35,840
so I stayed with him at the hospital.

181
00:16:35,920 --> 00:16:38,960
So I might not have seen the captain.

182
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:40,640
Anong,

183
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:43,400
you might be able to fool others,

184
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:45,240
but you can't fool me.

185
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:55,880
You've arrived?

186
00:16:57,160 --> 00:16:59,120
Alright, come in. I'll open the door.

187
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:01,920
Come in, come this way.

188
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:03,280
Hey, hello.

189
00:17:03,360 --> 00:17:04,400
Hello.

190
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:05,440
How have you been?

191
00:17:05,520 --> 00:17:07,720
- Good, good.
- Long time no see.

192
00:17:07,800 --> 00:17:08,720
Yeah.

193
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:10,040
You can stay for a while today, right?

194
00:17:10,119 --> 00:17:11,880
- Of course.
- Good.

195
00:17:11,960 --> 00:17:13,480
- I've prepared plenty of food. Please sit.
- Sounds great.

196
00:17:13,560 --> 00:17:15,160
Especially since she's not around.

197
00:17:15,240 --> 00:17:17,680
- I want to have a long talk with you.
- Mm.

198
00:17:18,440 --> 00:17:19,400
Good.

199
00:17:23,079 --> 00:17:24,800
Let's start with the first thing.

200
00:17:24,880 --> 00:17:26,480
- Go ahead.
- Is the DNA done?

201
00:17:27,079 --> 00:17:28,319
- It's done.
- About the divorce,

202
00:17:28,920 --> 00:17:30,320
I'll handle it for you.

203
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:34,200
Not a single baht will go to Anong.

204
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:36,880
Honestly,

205
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:39,760
I never thought
things would escalate this far,

206
00:17:39,840 --> 00:17:42,360
or that I'd have to deal
with all this again.

207
00:17:42,960 --> 00:17:47,120
But lately,
Anong's behavior has been strange.

208
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:51,400
Actually, I think it's been strange
since Prae passed away

209
00:17:51,480 --> 00:17:54,280
and you had to stay
in the hospital for a long time.

210
00:17:54,800 --> 00:17:55,840
<i>Listen to me.</i>

211
00:17:56,440 --> 00:17:57,840
Just endure a little longer.

212
00:17:58,440 --> 00:18:00,200
Everything will get better.

213
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:02,000
I promise.

214
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:03,440
No.

215
00:18:04,040 --> 00:18:05,840
I'm going to take Warat away from here.

216
00:18:05,920 --> 00:18:08,120
Then she passed away.

217
00:18:08,640 --> 00:18:11,200
And you got into an accident and had to
stay in the hospital for months.

218
00:18:11,960 --> 00:18:13,320
I remember it clearly.

219
00:18:15,280 --> 00:18:18,440
Anong was the one
who took care of everything,

220
00:18:18,520 --> 00:18:21,000
both the company and the house.

221
00:18:22,040 --> 00:18:22,920
Actually,

222
00:18:24,080 --> 00:18:25,800
I do see the good she's done.

223
00:18:27,960 --> 00:18:29,920
She's done a lot for me.

224
00:18:31,160 --> 00:18:32,240
That's why it's difficult.

225
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:34,640
It's difficult to decide on divorcing her.

226
00:18:35,720 --> 00:18:40,080
I hear she's been going
to some kind of treatment resort.

227
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:44,120
Her nephew Jirasin
has been trying his best to help her.

228
00:18:44,920 --> 00:18:46,920
But from what I see,

229
00:18:47,800 --> 00:18:50,280
she might claim mental illness.

230
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:53,800
If that's the case,

231
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:58,000
wouldn't that work in our favor?

232
00:19:03,560 --> 00:19:06,320
Mom, Mom. Arnon just called.

233
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:08,360
The unidentified bodies foundation
has sent back an update.

234
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:09,720
He's heading there now.

235
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:11,640
Calm down, speak slowly.

236
00:19:11,720 --> 00:19:13,720
You're going to run out of breath.

237
00:19:14,320 --> 00:19:16,960
I'm just excited.
Arnon, I'll hang up for now.

238
00:19:17,040 --> 00:19:19,480
I'll update Mom first.

239
00:19:19,560 --> 00:19:21,000
Okay. Drive safely.

240
00:19:23,080 --> 00:19:25,320
The housekeeper, Pong's older sister,

241
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:28,080
has already sent DNA samples
to compare with the victims

242
00:19:28,160 --> 00:19:30,160
from Kluay's car fire incident.

243
00:19:30,240 --> 00:19:33,640
It's really lucky
there's an organization that stores DNA.

244
00:19:33,720 --> 00:19:37,680
There must be
thousands of cases like ours.

245
00:19:37,760 --> 00:19:42,760
No wonder your dad
was so serious about this.

246
00:19:42,840 --> 00:19:45,840
Because it's not just for our family.

247
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:48,680
I'm proud

248
00:19:49,280 --> 00:19:51,680
to continue what Dad started.

249
00:19:55,240 --> 00:19:56,080
It's Arnon.

250
00:19:56,760 --> 00:19:58,160
Pick up.

251
00:19:58,240 --> 00:20:02,160
Hello, Arnon. How is it?
Do the DNA results match?

252
00:20:04,440 --> 00:20:06,520
This shouldn't have happened…

253
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:11,560
I've prepared
antiseptic mouthwash for you.

254
00:20:11,640 --> 00:20:14,200
Go rinse your mouth and treat your wound.

255
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:23,840
Kluay.

256
00:20:24,920 --> 00:20:27,400
You really don't believe that Ameena and I

257
00:20:28,040 --> 00:20:28,920
didn't do anything?

258
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:31,200
Didn't you say
you don't remember anything?

259
00:20:31,280 --> 00:20:32,480
I don't.

260
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:34,640
Go rinse your mouth and treat it.

261
00:20:36,320 --> 00:20:38,760
What I'm doing doesn't mean
I'm giving in to you.

262
00:20:39,280 --> 00:20:41,960
But we need to go tell your Grandma
that we're serious.

263
00:20:43,840 --> 00:20:47,240
I'm not going anywhere
until I've done what I promised you.

264
00:20:50,520 --> 00:20:51,520
Kluay.

265
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:55,040
Hey, Kluay.

266
00:20:56,840 --> 00:20:59,160
- What are you doing?
- Are you mad?

267
00:21:02,880 --> 00:21:06,720
Then… should we get engaged?

268
00:21:08,320 --> 00:21:09,480
What are you talking about?

269
00:21:10,600 --> 00:21:11,840
Since the moment…

270
00:21:14,120 --> 00:21:16,040
I asked to be serious with you,

271
00:21:18,520 --> 00:21:20,120
I've meant it.

272
00:21:26,120 --> 00:21:27,840
I really like you, Kluay.

273
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:34,320
I've never felt this way
about anyone before.

274
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:40,080
Every time I'm with you,
everything we do together…

275
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:46,000
it makes me so happy.

276
00:21:52,800 --> 00:21:53,800
Thank you

277
00:21:54,880 --> 00:21:57,280
for filling that part of me.

278
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:04,280
I've never been this happy before.

279
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:07,320
And I hope…

280
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:12,200
I can bring you happiness too.

281
00:22:19,680 --> 00:22:20,880
I like you.

282
00:22:40,760 --> 00:22:41,960
Please don't stay silent.

283
00:22:50,680 --> 00:22:51,560
Well…

284
00:22:57,200 --> 00:22:58,280
What?

285
00:23:00,120 --> 00:23:03,720
This is a big deal. Can I have…

286
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:05,000
a little time?

287
00:23:05,080 --> 00:23:06,320
It's too late.

288
00:23:06,840 --> 00:23:08,040
You have to answer right now.

289
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:12,240
Don't rush me.

290
00:23:12,760 --> 00:23:14,520
This is my whole life.

291
00:23:16,600 --> 00:23:17,760
Mine too.

292
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:33,120
Do you

293
00:23:34,640 --> 00:23:35,680
like me?

294
00:23:41,680 --> 00:23:43,680
If you don't answer,
I'll take that as a yes.

295
00:23:43,760 --> 00:23:44,840
Hey.

296
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:46,960
You can't do that.

297
00:23:47,720 --> 00:23:49,640
Like I said,

298
00:23:50,320 --> 00:23:51,760
this is something really important.

299
00:23:51,840 --> 00:23:54,480
Don't just decide for me.

300
00:23:57,720 --> 00:23:58,760
Alright then.

301
00:24:00,560 --> 00:24:03,560
If you wear the ring, that means

302
00:24:03,640 --> 00:24:04,760
you're okay with it.

303
00:24:08,440 --> 00:24:09,960
If you're shy, I won't look.

304
00:24:18,760 --> 00:24:20,200
Left hand.

305
00:24:42,880 --> 00:24:45,960
Let's go. Are you shy?

306
00:24:47,120 --> 00:24:48,160
Are you?

307
00:24:50,160 --> 00:24:51,200
You're crazy.

308
00:24:52,640 --> 00:24:55,000
Are you two engaged now?

309
00:24:59,080 --> 00:25:00,440
This is a ring I treasure deeply.

310
00:25:04,320 --> 00:25:07,720
No need to ask where it came from, right?

311
00:25:09,240 --> 00:25:11,240
Ms. Praewilai's ring.

312
00:25:11,320 --> 00:25:12,640
I remember it.

313
00:25:14,720 --> 00:25:17,680
So I'm definitely not joking about this.

314
00:25:19,080 --> 00:25:20,280
No questions, right?

315
00:25:21,680 --> 00:25:23,880
With the utmost respect,
you can't stop Madam

316
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:25,640
from worrying about you two.

317
00:25:26,160 --> 00:25:27,760
If the case about the thief
at Ms. Kluay's house

318
00:25:27,840 --> 00:25:30,160
is still unresolved,
that means it's not over yet.

319
00:25:30,880 --> 00:25:33,640
Mr. Supol,
it's my duty to look after Kluay.

320
00:25:34,240 --> 00:25:37,160
I'm not going to let Kluay
be like what Grandma thought.

321
00:25:37,240 --> 00:25:38,320
Yes, sir.

322
00:25:38,880 --> 00:25:42,160
Then I'll go inform Madam again.

323
00:25:45,240 --> 00:25:46,720
Mr. Supol,

324
00:25:46,800 --> 00:25:50,080
I'm sorry
for putting you in a difficult position.

325
00:25:51,080 --> 00:25:54,760
I feel bad too
for having to go against Grandma's orders,

326
00:25:54,840 --> 00:25:58,480
when everything she did
was out of love and concern for Warat.

327
00:26:00,240 --> 00:26:01,600
But I promise

328
00:26:01,680 --> 00:26:05,720
to resolve all of this
as quickly as possible,

329
00:26:05,800 --> 00:26:07,600
so that Warat

330
00:26:08,120 --> 00:26:09,680
won't have to face
this kind of danger anymore.

331
00:26:20,520 --> 00:26:22,760
What are you doing, Mr. Supol?

332
00:26:22,840 --> 00:26:23,920
Taking notes.

333
00:26:24,640 --> 00:26:26,280
Every word you said

334
00:26:26,360 --> 00:26:28,800
was sharp and precise.
I'm going to report it to Madam.

335
00:26:28,880 --> 00:26:30,800
I really can't remember it.
Do you know why?

336
00:26:31,760 --> 00:26:32,760
Because I'm old now.

337
00:26:35,920 --> 00:26:36,880
Hey.

338
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:37,960
What are you laughing at?

339
00:26:38,040 --> 00:26:40,440
- Hey.
- What did he say? What did he say?

340
00:26:41,840 --> 00:26:43,040
Hey, Mr. Supol.

341
00:26:43,120 --> 00:26:44,680
- Yes?
- Are you crying?

342
00:26:45,280 --> 00:26:46,120
Uh.

343
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:49,560
No… no, I'm not crying.

344
00:26:50,200 --> 00:26:51,880
Oh, it's that line, isn't it?

345
00:26:51,960 --> 00:26:52,880
What line?

346
00:26:52,960 --> 00:26:54,560
- Don't say it.
- Yes.

347
00:26:54,640 --> 00:26:57,640
"Dust got in my eyes."
Just like in dramas.

348
00:26:57,720 --> 00:26:59,160
Don't tease him.

349
00:26:59,240 --> 00:27:02,760
Wait, wait. Please let me
switch back to serious mode first.

350
00:27:02,840 --> 00:27:05,680
If Madam finds out, she'll scold me.

351
00:27:05,760 --> 00:27:06,760
Okay.

352
00:27:09,360 --> 00:27:10,320
Go on.

353
00:27:11,320 --> 00:27:15,000
I have something important
to tell you, Mr. Warat.

354
00:27:15,080 --> 00:27:16,680
Oh, Ms. Kluay should hear this too.

355
00:27:16,760 --> 00:27:18,120
That's alright.

356
00:27:18,200 --> 00:27:20,160
Please go ahead and speak with Warat.

357
00:27:20,240 --> 00:27:22,040
- I'll wait outside.
- It's okay, babe.

358
00:27:22,880 --> 00:27:25,520
There are no secrets left
between us anymore.

359
00:27:26,800 --> 00:27:28,040
Hm.

360
00:27:32,760 --> 00:27:36,120
This is a circular notice
to all members of the Vanich family

361
00:27:36,200 --> 00:27:39,280
regarding the opening
of Chairwoman Wanee's will.

362
00:27:39,800 --> 00:27:42,000
Madam asked me to inform you

363
00:27:42,080 --> 00:27:47,080
that the first heir
of the Vanich family is you, Mr. Warat.

364
00:27:48,080 --> 00:27:50,960
Is Grandma really that worried
that I won't attend the meeting?

365
00:27:51,040 --> 00:27:52,120
DAD

366
00:27:55,160 --> 00:27:56,000
Yes, Dad?

367
00:27:56,520 --> 00:27:59,040
<i>You knew it was me.</i>
<i>Why didn't you answer the phone?</i>

368
00:27:59,560 --> 00:28:02,280
Because I knew it was you.
I didn't want to talk.

369
00:28:02,360 --> 00:28:03,480
<i>Ameena.</i>

370
00:28:05,840 --> 00:28:07,320
I'm sorry.

371
00:28:08,560 --> 00:28:11,560
What is it? I'm busy.

372
00:28:12,560 --> 00:28:15,880
<i>My source told me</i>
<i>that Mrs. Wanee is about to open her will.</i>

373
00:28:18,040 --> 00:28:20,400
What does that have to do with us?

374
00:28:20,480 --> 00:28:22,880
<i>It does. It matters a lot.</i>

375
00:28:22,960 --> 00:28:25,960
<i>Do you know who her first heir is?</i>

376
00:28:26,040 --> 00:28:27,280
Warat, I guess.

377
00:28:27,360 --> 00:28:31,480
<i>Good. Then remember this.</i>
<i>Don't cause any more trouble with Warat.</i>

378
00:28:31,560 --> 00:28:33,840
<i>He's about to take control</i>

379
00:28:33,920 --> 00:28:36,040
<i>of almost all</i>
<i>of Vanich's power and assets.</i>

380
00:28:36,120 --> 00:28:39,160
<i>This isn't just about the merger</i>
<i>of our department store with theirs.</i>

381
00:28:39,240 --> 00:28:42,080
<i>You have to get as much benefit</i>
<i>out of him as possible.</i>

382
00:28:43,280 --> 00:28:44,120
Yes.

383
00:28:54,560 --> 00:28:57,480
The DNA results between you
and Mr. Sarut are out already.

384
00:28:57,560 --> 00:28:58,960
What are you still worried about?

385
00:28:59,640 --> 00:29:04,280
I don't know. I just feel like
there's something strange

386
00:29:06,480 --> 00:29:08,080
about Grandma opening the will.

387
00:29:10,160 --> 00:29:11,880
Did you get another sign?

388
00:29:12,560 --> 00:29:13,560
No.

389
00:29:14,240 --> 00:29:17,560
But your signs are accurate, though.

390
00:29:18,520 --> 00:29:19,400
Kluay,

391
00:29:20,080 --> 00:29:24,160
I said there was no sign,
so there's no sign. If you think there is,

392
00:29:24,920 --> 00:29:26,160
then there will be one.

393
00:29:27,440 --> 00:29:29,200
DNA LAB

394
00:29:31,320 --> 00:29:32,440
Do you want to answer that?

395
00:29:33,080 --> 00:29:33,920
It's the lab.

396
00:29:35,560 --> 00:29:37,960
You're still not done?

397
00:29:38,480 --> 00:29:39,520
Another one.

398
00:29:40,720 --> 00:29:44,040
Wow. Seriously?

399
00:29:44,120 --> 00:29:45,920
Besides the lab I found,

400
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:48,240
you sent it somewhere else too?

401
00:29:51,200 --> 00:29:52,960
It's called being thorough.

402
00:29:56,880 --> 00:29:59,880
Since we're already out,

403
00:29:59,960 --> 00:30:01,560
I can check it when we get inside.

404
00:30:01,640 --> 00:30:03,280
That's good.

405
00:30:03,360 --> 00:30:06,440
At least you have someone
to compare DNA with.

406
00:30:12,240 --> 00:30:15,920
Actually, before all this,
I never wondered who I was.

407
00:30:16,720 --> 00:30:19,240
But when I found out I was the target

408
00:30:19,320 --> 00:30:21,320
of the thief who broke into Baan Saeng,

409
00:30:21,840 --> 00:30:25,160
that's when I started wanting to know
who I really am.

410
00:30:29,840 --> 00:30:31,000
But that's the thing.

411
00:30:31,520 --> 00:30:33,600
I don't know where to begin,

412
00:30:33,680 --> 00:30:35,640
I don't know what to do,

413
00:30:36,440 --> 00:30:38,320
or whether I should just let it go.

414
00:30:40,400 --> 00:30:41,640
What do you think?

415
00:30:43,760 --> 00:30:44,840
It's good.

416
00:30:47,640 --> 00:30:50,120
We should know who we are.

417
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:52,400
But most importantly,

418
00:30:53,440 --> 00:30:55,200
your safety

419
00:30:56,720 --> 00:30:57,880
has to come first.

420
00:30:59,720 --> 00:31:00,880
It's okay.

421
00:31:01,400 --> 00:31:05,200
Maybe the information Grandma got
was inaccurate. Right?

422
00:31:05,880 --> 00:31:08,000
Should we go inside?
So you can check your email too.

423
00:31:08,080 --> 00:31:08,920
It's fine.

424
00:31:09,440 --> 00:31:12,760
Even if you already got results from
the other lab, you should still check it.

425
00:31:12,840 --> 00:31:13,920
You already paid for it.

426
00:31:17,280 --> 00:31:18,400
So stingy.

427
00:31:19,280 --> 00:31:20,240
Mr. Warat.

428
00:31:21,760 --> 00:31:24,400
It cost so much already.

429
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:25,920
How is that stingy?

430
00:31:34,400 --> 00:31:35,240
Arnon.

431
00:31:35,760 --> 00:31:37,920
- Are you sure about the results?
- Mm-hm.

432
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:39,720
- Oh, Mom. Hello.
- Hello.

433
00:31:39,800 --> 00:31:42,280
Have a seat, Mr. Arnon. Hey, Som,

434
00:31:42,880 --> 00:31:45,520
don't interrogate him yet.
He just got back and must be tired.

435
00:31:45,600 --> 00:31:47,040
Here's the situation.

436
00:31:47,120 --> 00:31:50,040
The DNA of Pong's older sister

437
00:31:50,120 --> 00:31:55,920
does not match the bodies
from the accident that day with Kluay.

438
00:31:57,280 --> 00:31:58,960
So that means

439
00:31:59,040 --> 00:32:01,240
the people we suspected,
the ones who took Kluay,

440
00:32:01,320 --> 00:32:03,600
weren't Pong and Soi,

441
00:32:04,120 --> 00:32:05,760
Anong's people?

442
00:32:05,840 --> 00:32:08,960
Maybe yes, maybe no.

443
00:32:09,560 --> 00:32:12,280
I don't get it.
Why are you being so vague, Arnon?

444
00:32:12,360 --> 00:32:15,120
Can you just say it straight?

445
00:32:15,200 --> 00:32:16,400
Som.

446
00:32:16,480 --> 00:32:19,760
Why are you pressuring him like that?

447
00:32:19,840 --> 00:32:23,760
Here's the thing. That accident,
the car crash and fire,

448
00:32:23,840 --> 00:32:25,000
there were over ten victims.

449
00:32:25,600 --> 00:32:26,600
Ten?

450
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:29,120
And back then, the system

451
00:32:29,200 --> 00:32:32,840
for handling unidentified bodies
wasn't as good as it is now.

452
00:32:32,920 --> 00:32:35,200
So that means we have to compare

453
00:32:35,280 --> 00:32:38,520
Pong's sister's DNA
with almost everybody from that day?

454
00:32:38,600 --> 00:32:39,960
More or less, yeah.

455
00:32:40,040 --> 00:32:43,760
I knew it. There's no way
we'd get lucky that easily.

456
00:32:44,760 --> 00:32:45,920
It's okay.

457
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:49,160
At least we still have hope.

458
00:32:49,240 --> 00:32:52,600
They never said
there's nothing left for us to test.

459
00:32:52,680 --> 00:32:53,840
That's right.

460
00:32:54,440 --> 00:32:58,440
You two really get along.

461
00:32:58,520 --> 00:32:59,600
I'll call Kluay.

462
00:32:59,680 --> 00:33:01,480
- Hey, no, no.
- You can't.

463
00:33:02,000 --> 00:33:02,840
Why not?

464
00:33:02,920 --> 00:33:04,160
What do you want to talk about?

465
00:33:04,240 --> 00:33:07,640
I'm just going to ask her
to buy snacks from Phetchaburi.

466
00:33:07,720 --> 00:33:09,040
It's on the way.

467
00:33:46,600 --> 00:33:47,720
You're back?

468
00:33:48,720 --> 00:33:50,280
I thought you were going to stay at home.

469
00:33:52,680 --> 00:33:54,200
I forgot some work on my computer.

470
00:33:56,680 --> 00:33:58,160
So it's important work

471
00:33:58,680 --> 00:34:00,320
that made you come back.

472
00:34:09,120 --> 00:34:11,360
So, you still don't believe me, right?

473
00:34:11,960 --> 00:34:14,560
That Warat and I
really didn't do anything?

474
00:34:14,639 --> 00:34:15,800
I don't want to talk.

475
00:34:15,880 --> 00:34:18,040
If you don't want to talk,
how are we supposed to live together?

476
00:34:18,639 --> 00:34:19,840
Just walking past each other

477
00:34:20,440 --> 00:34:23,159
without talking? Are you crazy?

478
00:34:23,239 --> 00:34:24,080
Don't you think you're being cruel?

479
00:34:24,159 --> 00:34:26,480
Try looking at what you've done.

480
00:34:26,560 --> 00:34:27,560
What if it were the other way around?

481
00:34:28,080 --> 00:34:30,600
If you saw what I saw,
went through what I went through,

482
00:34:30,679 --> 00:34:32,280
you probably would've killed me by now.

483
00:34:32,360 --> 00:34:34,360
I already told you why I did it.

484
00:34:34,880 --> 00:34:35,719
What more do you want?

485
00:34:35,800 --> 00:34:38,000
So just having a reason makes it okay?

486
00:34:38,520 --> 00:34:41,000
Having a reason makes you a good person?

487
00:34:41,520 --> 00:34:44,560
It's because you think like this
that you've become this way.

488
00:34:44,639 --> 00:34:46,159
Are you insulting me?

489
00:34:46,760 --> 00:34:49,040
I forgot. It's my mistake.

490
00:34:49,560 --> 00:34:53,120
There's no point talking to you.
Nothing will ever change.

491
00:34:53,199 --> 00:34:55,120
It just gets worse and worse.

492
00:34:58,000 --> 00:34:58,840
Det.

493
00:35:01,120 --> 00:35:02,520
Stop right now.

494
00:35:04,720 --> 00:35:06,480
We need to talk.

495
00:35:09,520 --> 00:35:11,520
Why does he keep calling?

496
00:35:13,520 --> 00:35:16,920
Yes, Dad. I'll do everything you told me.

497
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:18,280
I gotta go.

498
00:35:20,440 --> 00:35:21,280
Det.

499
00:35:21,800 --> 00:35:23,240
I said… Ouch!

500
00:35:26,120 --> 00:35:27,160
Det!

501
00:35:38,560 --> 00:35:39,520
Fine.

502
00:35:40,840 --> 00:35:42,680
You want me to be the villain so badly?

503
00:35:43,560 --> 00:35:44,680
Yeah.

504
00:35:44,760 --> 00:35:45,840
Fine.

505
00:37:33,000 --> 00:37:35,000
Does anyone else act like you, Kluay?

506
00:37:38,440 --> 00:37:40,800
Morning, my fiancée.

507
00:37:44,280 --> 00:37:47,800
DNA LAB

508
00:37:53,680 --> 00:37:56,480
You should wait until the truth
about Ms. Waree is clear first.

509
00:37:56,560 --> 00:37:59,400
No matter what, Ms. Waree is still
your real granddaughter.

510
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:02,000
And Warat is my real grandson too.

511
00:38:02,080 --> 00:38:03,360
NEXT EPISODE

512
00:38:03,440 --> 00:38:05,040
<i>Being together feels so good.</i>

513
00:38:06,160 --> 00:38:07,960
If I had known,
I would've asked you out sooner.

514
00:38:10,240 --> 00:38:11,560
<i>Sin…</i>

515
00:38:12,240 --> 00:38:14,760
How could you leave me here like this?

516
00:38:14,840 --> 00:38:18,280
On the will opening day, you have to come.

517
00:38:19,760 --> 00:38:21,080
<i>I just don't understand</i>

518
00:38:21,600 --> 00:38:23,920
<i>why Sin has to act like this.</i>

519
00:38:24,440 --> 00:38:25,840
Do you really feel no guilt at all?

520
00:38:25,920 --> 00:38:27,560
Warat,

521
00:38:27,640 --> 00:38:30,640
you're seriously misunderstanding me.

522
00:38:31,240 --> 00:38:32,920
I really didn't do anything.

523
00:40:56,880 --> 00:40:58,720
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
